2026-04-21 02:47:07 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1 LED', 'Control Module 2 LED', 'Control Module 3 LED', 'Control Module 4 LED', 'Control Module 5 LED', 'Control Module 6 LED', 'Control Module 7 LED', 'Control Module 8 LED'] hypothesis_explanation='All eight control module indicator LEDs have been physically removed. In this circuit design, removing the LEDs (which are in series with resistors, forming a current path between the 12V and 0V lines within each module) breaks the parallel current paths in each control module. This creates an open parallel path in every control module, effectively interrupting the series electrical path and preventing current from reaching the lamp or indicator in the load module. Since all external and internal wiring has been verified intact, and the power supply LED is on, the only circuit-level abnormality reported is the total absence of all eight control module indicator LEDs. Their removal thus causes an open circuit at each corresponding module, making it impossible for current to flow through the load regardless of switch position. Reinstalling those LEDs (or bridging their connection points) is required to restore system functionality.'
